body:
Hey guys,

Just idling away my time at work thinking about league and i had a thought about an interesting game mode (Riot made or player attempted in a custom match without a formal game mode)

Essentially - we now have 5 headhunter skins released - {{champion:107}} Rengar, {{champion:11}} Master Yi, {{champion:76}} Nidalee, {{champion:51}} Caitlyn and {{champion:84}} Akali. These guys could be one team (A FIXED, unchangable team - headhunter skins given temporarily like in Nemesis Draft - but without the RP cost)

We also have a number of &#039;operative&#039; type skins on other champions - Commando skins, Special Ops, Omega Squad, etc.

Well, my idea isnt just listing skins - my idea is to have a &#039;Hunt&#039; game mode where the Headhunters face off against a random selection of 5 champs with these operative skins. It would become something like the movie Predators where a bunch of specialist people from around the world are dropped into a predator hunting ground.

In my opinion - people are too familiar with Summoners Rift - and so for the sake of Hunting and such, i propose making Twisted Tree line the Hunting Ground for this mode.

The &#039;Hunters&#039; i.e the Head Hunters Team could get a slight advantage (Maybe level advantage or Hunting Ground Buffs?) - especially as they would have a handicap of 1-2 less players as opposed to the team they VS. Towers would (if possible) be removed and the aim is to play an &#039;elimination&#039; style or &#039;juggernaut&#039; style game.

Well - there you have it, its nothing fancy, just a little idea i had while at work.

I dont expect anything will come of it, but i just wanted to voice my idea!

Who knows, maybe the experience and opinionated community could flash it out more fully if they so desired - or smash it to pieces too - i dont mind :)

Take care!

